title: Showreel 2009
description:
This video highlights the areas of personal strength and experience: from being a producer, graphic designer, 2D animator, lighting, shot composition, and simply editing.

Most examples are local commercials and music videos that I've worked on (in some aspect) since June 2007.

Footage features: HVX200, SGPro 35mm, Adobe After Effects CS3, Adobe Illustrator CS3, and Zaxwerks 3D Invigorator.


Music: Hell Yeah by Zebrahead

title: Big Apple Grapple - Open
description:
This is the rough build for the Big Apple Grapple - Arm Wrestling Competition.

Created entirely in After Effects CS3 using footage shot on multiple Panasonic HVX-200s.

This build contains some timing errors and few incorrect composition sizes.

title: Popmart Commercial
description:
Spring 2006. This is the first edit for a class assignment. The concept was to make a commercial for a local business. 

Who knew I'd wind up as a producer at a production company doing commercials. Ironnnny.

title: Stroke Awareness PSA
description:
This isn't a real PSA for the ASA, but we certainly pitched it to them. This was a project junior year of college. Spring of 2006. 

My friend Jill was the director.  I was the camera op and editor for this. Jeff Hartney was our voice over.

 Created for educational purposes only.
